    "Other highly prevalent cargo functions included a wide diversity of cellular and metabolic pathways defined in the COG (Fig. 5b) and Kyoto Encyclopedia of Genes and Genomes (KEGG) databases (Supplementary Fig.",
    "The most enriched among these was transfer RNA modification, encoded in 35 compound plasmids within different systems.",
    "For example, the globally prevalent system PS1110 (present in 739 metagenomes) contained 291 compound plasmids (27 non-redundant), three of which encoded an enzyme that performs tRNA Gm18 2′-O-methylation (COG0566) and were collectively present in 498 metagenomes (Supplementary Fig. 14 and Supplementary Table 11)."
